Equation 4.11 can be written directly without the intermediate steps represented by equations 4.9 and 4.10. This is achieved by treating nodes 2 and 3 as a single supernode and summing the currents away from the node based on \(v_2\) and \(v_3\). Figure 4.15 depicts this method.

